  "raw_meta_yaml": "{% set name = \"elegant\" %}\n{% set version = \"2026.1.0\" %}\n{% set sdds_version = \"5.10\" %}\n{% set build = 0 %}\n\npackage:\n  name: {{ name|lower }}\n  version: {{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  - url: https://github.com/rtsoliday/elegant/archive/refs/tags/elegant-{{ version }}.tar.gz\n    sha256: 6464d74a178bdd4ffb7cbf452bdc5e8fa384a3dcc0740bf443500b945704a96c\n    folder: elegant\n  # TODO: this should be split to a separate feedstock now...\n  - url: https://github.com/rtsoliday/SDDS/archive/refs/tags/SDDS-{{ sdds_version }}.tar.gz\n    sha256: 322aec6b5c9d2e620d5252a275dbf8c8dbfe53f58391aed8c30e610f7bc4ec62\n    folder: SDDS\n  # Standalone nlpp (namelist preprocessor) for cross-compilation:\n  - url: https://github.com/ken-lauer/sdds-nlpp/archive/refs/tags/v0.0.1.tar.gz\n    sha256: b895864408b607aab66f753db2904f7d2157adc306c61b2d6498f7b6bdb81a2e\n    folder: nlpp_standalone\n\nbuild:\n  skip: true  # [win]\n  number: {{ build }}\n  string: \"mpi_{{ mpi }}_h{{ PKG_HASH }}_{{ build }}\"\n  run_exports:\n    - {{ name }} * mpi_{{ mpi }}_*\n  ignore_run_exports:\n    - libaec  # [linux]\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - {{ compiler(\"c\") }}\n    - {{ stdlib(\"c\") }}\n    - {{ compiler(\"cxx\") }}\n    - {{ compiler(\"fortran\") }}\n    - {{ mpi }}\n    # TODO: v2.5.1 libfabric complaining about getrandom/glibc 2.25\n    - libfabric <2.5.1  # [linux and mpi == \"mpich\"]\n    - make\n  host:\n    - eigen\n    - fftw * mpi_{{ mpi }}_*\n    - gsl\n    - hdf5 * mpi_{{ mpi }}_*\n    - libaec\n    - libgd\n    - libgomp  # [linux]\n    - liblzma-devel\n    - libpng\n    - libtiff\n    - zlib\n    - zstd  # [osx]\n    # tiff transitive deps directly linked on macOS:\n    - lerc  # [osx]\n    - libdeflate  # [osx]\n    - libjpeg-turbo  # [osx]\n    - {{ mpi }}\n    - liblapack\n    - liblapacke\n    - libblas\n    - openblas\n    # Fortran runtime directly linked on macOS:\n    - libgfortran  # [osx]\n  run:\n    - {{ mpi }}\n    - libblas * *openblas\n    - libcblas * *openblas\n    - zstd  # [osx]\n    - openblas\n    # Saw this overlinker error in cppbmad-feedstock, too - this is due to\n    # gfortran, and only on macos:\n    - libgcc     # [osx]\n\ntest:\n  commands:\n    # Set up for OpenMPI testing:\n    - export OMPI_MCA_plm=isolated                          # [mpi == \"openmpi\"]\n    - export OMPI_MCA_btl_vader_single_copy_mechanism=none  # [mpi == \"openmpi\"]\n    - export OMPI_MCA_rmaps_base_oversubscribe=yes          # [mpi == \"openmpi\"]\n    # Check that elegant and Pelegant are executable:\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/Pelegant\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/elegant\n    - elegant\n    # Key SDDS tools:\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsprocess\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsplot\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/rpn\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddscontour\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddspseudoinverse\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/hdf2sdds\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sdds2hdf\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsbrightness\n    # A sampling of other expected binaries:\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsconvert\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddscombine\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsfft\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsinterp\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddsquery\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/sddssort\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/elegantto\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/nlpp\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/editstring\n    - test -f $PREFIX/bin/timeconvert\n\nabout:\n  home: https://github.com/rtsoliday/elegant\n  license: EPICS\n  license_file:\n    - elegant/LICENSE\n    - SDDS/meschach/LICENSE\n    - SDDS/xlslib/LICENSE\n    - SDDS/pgapack/COPYING\n  summary: |\n    Pelegant is Parallel Elegant, a parallelized accelerator code that\n    computes beta functions, matrices, orbits, floor coordinates, amplification\n    factors, dynamic aperture, and more\n  description: |\n    Elegant is an accelerator code that computes beta functions, matrices,\n    orbits, floor coordinates, amplification factors, dynamic aperture, and\n    more. It does 6-D tracking with matrices and/or canonical integrators, and\n    supports a variety of time-dependent elements. It also does optimization\n    (e.g., matching), including optimization of tracking results. It is the\n    principle accelerator code used at APS.\n  doc_url: https://ops.aps.anl.gov/manuals/elegant_latest/elegant.html\n  dev_url: https://github.com/rtsoliday/elegant\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - ken-lauer\n",
